#. <section class="sutta" id="mn73"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn73:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 73"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 73"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn73:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvacchasutta"
msgstr "The Longer Discourse With Vacchagotta"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn73:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho vacchagotto paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then the wanderer Vacchagotta went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings "
"with him."

msgctxt "mn73:2.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to the Buddha:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:3.1"
msgid "“dīgharattāhaṃ bhotā gotamena sahakathī."
msgstr "“For a long time I have had discussions with Master Gotama."

msgctxt "mn73:3.2"
msgid "Sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo saṃkhittena kusalākusalaṃ desetū”ti."
msgstr "Please teach me in brief what is skillful and what is unskillful.”"

msgctxt "mn73:3.3"
msgid ""
"“Saṃkhittenapi kho te ahaṃ, vaccha, kusalākusalaṃ deseyyaṃ, vitthārenapi kho "
"te ahaṃ, vaccha, kusalākusalaṃ deseyyaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“Vaccha, I can teach you what is skillful and what is unskillful in brief or "
"in detail."

msgctxt "mn73:3.4"
msgid "api ca te ahaṃ, vaccha, saṃkhittena kusalākusalaṃ desessāmi."
msgstr "Still, let me do so in brief."

msgctxt "mn73:3.5"
msgid "Taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn73:3.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Vaccha replied."

msgctxt "mn73:3.7"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:4.1"
msgid "“Lobho kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, alobho kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "“Greed is unskillful, contentment is skillful."

msgctxt "mn73:4.2"
msgid "doso kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, adoso kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "Hate is unskillful, love is skillful."

msgctxt "mn73:4.3"
msgid "moho kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, amoho kusalaṃ."
msgstr "Delusion is unskillful, understanding is skillful."

msgctxt "mn73:4.4"
msgid "Iti kho, vaccha, ime tayo dhammā akusalā, tayo dhammā kusalā."
msgstr "So there are these three unskillful things and three that are skillful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.490"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:5.1"
msgid "Pāṇātipāto kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, pāṇātipātā veramaṇī kusalaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; speech that’s "
"false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; covetousness, ill will, and wrong "
"view: these things are unskillful."

msgctxt "mn73:5.2"
msgid "adinnādānaṃ kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, adinnādānā veramaṇī kusalaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Refraining from killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; "
"refraining from speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; "
"contentment, kind-heartedness, and right view: these things are skillful."

msgctxt "mn73:5.3"
msgid ""
"kāmesumicchācāro kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī kusalaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:5.4"
msgid "musāvādo kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, musāvādā veramaṇī kusalaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:5.5"
msgid "pisuṇā vācā kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī kusalaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:5.6"
msgid "pharusā vācā kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī kusalaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:5.7"
msgid "samphappalāpo kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, samphappalāpā veramaṇī kusalaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:5.8"
msgid "abhijjhā kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, anabhijjhā kusalaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:5.9"
msgid "byāpādo kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, abyāpādo kusalaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:5.10"
msgid "micchādiṭṭhi kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ sammādiṭṭhi kusalaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:5.11"
msgid "Iti kho, vaccha, ime dasa dhammā akusalā, dasa dhammā kusalā."
msgstr "So there are these ten unskillful things and ten that are skillful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:6.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, vaccha, bhikkhuno taṇhā pahīnā hoti ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā "
"anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā, so hoti bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo "
"vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano "
"sammadaññāvimutto”ti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant has given up craving so it is cut off at the root, made "
"like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future, that "
"mendicant is perfected. They’ve ended the defilements, completed the "
"spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved "
"their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and are rightly "
"freed through enlightenment.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:7.1"
msgid "“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo."
msgstr "“Leaving aside Master Gotama,"

#. VAR: sāvako yo āsavānaṃ khayā → sāvako āsavānaṃ khayā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn73:7.2"
msgid ""
"Atthi pana te bhoto gotamassa ekabhikkhupi sāvako yo āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"is there even a single monk disciple of Master Gotama who has realized the "
"undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and "
"lives having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of "
"defilements?”"

msgctxt "mn73:7.3"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri "
"satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye bhikkhū mama sāvakā āsavānaṃ "
"khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There are not just one hundred such monks who are my disciples, Vaccha, or "
"two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:8.1"
msgid "“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū."
msgstr "“Leaving aside Master Gotama and the monks,"

msgctxt "mn73:8.2"
msgid ""
"Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekā bhikkhunīpi sāvikā yā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"is there even a single nun disciple of Master Gotama who has realized the "
"undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and "
"lives having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of "
"defilements?”"

msgctxt "mn73:8.3"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri "
"satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova yā bhikkhuniyo mama sāvikā "
"āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There are not just one hundred such nuns who are my disciples, Vaccha, or "
"two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.491"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:9.1"
msgid "“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo."
msgstr "“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, and the nuns,"

msgctxt "mn73:9.2"
msgid ""
"Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsakopi sāvako gihī odātavasano brahmacārī yo "
"pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha "
"parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"is there even a single layman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed and "
"celibate—who, with the ending of the five lower fetters, is reborn "
"spontaneously, to be extinguished there, not liable to return from that "
"world?”"

msgctxt "mn73:9.3"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri "
"satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye upāsakā mama sāvakā gihī "
"odātavasanā brahmacārino pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"opapātikā tattha parinibbāyino anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There are not just one hundred such celibate laymen who are my disciples, "
"Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:10.1"
msgid ""
"“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo, tiṭṭhantu "
"upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino."
msgstr ""
"“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, the nuns, and the celibate laymen,"

msgctxt "mn73:10.2"
msgid ""
"Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsakopi sāvako gihī odātavasano kāmabhogī "
"sāsanakaro ovādappaṭikaro yo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṅkatho "
"vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane viharatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"is there even a single layman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed, "
"enjoying sensual pleasures, following instructions, and responding to advice—"
"who has gone beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and lives self-assured and "
"independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instruction?”"

msgctxt "mn73:10.3"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri "
"satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye upāsakā mama sāvakā gihī "
"odātavasanā kāmabhogino sāsanakarā ovādappaṭikarā tiṇṇavicikicchā "
"vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane viharantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There are not just one hundred such laymen enjoying sensual pleasures who "
"are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many "
"more than that.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:11.1"
msgid ""
"“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo, tiṭṭhantu "
"upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā "
"kāmabhogino."
msgstr ""
"“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, the nuns, the celibate laymen, and "
"the laymen enjoying sensual pleasures,"

msgctxt "mn73:11.2"
msgid ""
"Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsikāpi sāvikā gihinī odātavasanā "
"brahmacārinī yā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā "
"tattha parinibbāyinī anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"is there even a single laywoman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed and "
"celibate—who, with the ending of the five lower fetters, is reborn "
"spontaneously, to be extinguished there, not liable to return from that "
"world?”"

msgctxt "mn73:11.3"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri "
"satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova yā upāsikā mama sāvikā gihiniyo "
"odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"opapātikā tattha parinibbāyiniyo anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There are not just one hundred such celibate laywomen who are my disciples, "
"Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:12.1"
msgid ""
"“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo, tiṭṭhantu "
"upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā "
"kāmabhogino, tiṭṭhantu upāsikā gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo."
msgstr ""
"“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, the nuns, the celibate laymen, the "
"laymen enjoying sensual pleasures, and the celibate laywomen,"

msgctxt "mn73:12.2"
msgid ""
"Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsikāpi sāvikā gihinī odātavasanā kāmabhoginī "
"sāsanakarā ovādappaṭikarā yā tiṇṇavicikicchā vigatakathaṅkathā "
"vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane viharatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"is there even a single laywoman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed, "
"enjoying sensual pleasures, following instructions, and responding to advice—"
"who has gone beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and lives self-assured and "
"independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instruction?”"

msgctxt "mn73:12.3"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri "
"satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova yā upāsikā mama sāvikā gihiniyo "
"odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo sāsanakarā ovādappaṭikarā tiṇṇavicikicchā "
"vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane viharantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There are not just one hundred such laywomen enjoying sensual pleasures who "
"are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many "
"more than that.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.492"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:13.1"
msgid ""
"“Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavaṃyeva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, no "
"ca kho bhikkhū ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"“If Master Gotama was the only one to succeed in this teaching, not any "
"monks,"

msgctxt "mn73:13.2"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena."
msgstr "then this spiritual path would be incomplete in that respect."

msgctxt "mn73:13.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako bhikkhū ca "
"ārādhakā;"
msgstr ""
"But because both Master Gotama and monks have succeeded in this teaching,"

msgctxt "mn73:13.4"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena."
msgstr "this spiritual path is complete in that respect."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:13.5"
msgid ""
"Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, "
"bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho bhikkhuniyo ārādhikā "
"abhavissaṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"If Master Gotama and the monks were the only ones to succeed in this "
"teaching, not any nuns …"

msgctxt "mn73:13.6"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:13.7"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū "
"ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:13.8"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:13.9"
msgid ""
"Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, "
"bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, no "
"ca kho upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu;"
msgstr "celibate laymen …"

msgctxt "mn73:13.10"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:13.11"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū "
"ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā "
"brahmacārino ārādhakā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:13.12"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:13.13"
msgid ""
"Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, "
"bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, "
"upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho "
"upāsakā gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu;"
msgstr "laymen enjoying sensual pleasures …"

msgctxt "mn73:13.14"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:13.15"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū "
"ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā "
"brahmacārino ārādhakā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:13.16"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.493"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:13.17"
msgid ""
"Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, "
"bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, "
"upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, upāsakā ca "
"gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho upāsikā "
"gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu;"
msgstr "celibate laywomen …"

msgctxt "mn73:13.18"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:13.19"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū "
"ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā "
"brahmacārino ārādhakā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā, "
"upāsikā ca gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo ārādhikā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn73:13.20"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:13.21"
msgid ""
"Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, "
"bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, "
"upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, upāsakā ca "
"gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, upāsikā ca gihiniyo "
"odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho upāsikā gihiniyo "
"odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu;"
msgstr "laywomen enjoying sensual pleasures,"

msgctxt "mn73:13.22"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena."
msgstr "then this spiritual path would be incomplete in that respect."

msgctxt "mn73:13.23"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū "
"ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā "
"brahmacārino ārādhakā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā, "
"upāsikā ca gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo ārādhikā, upāsikā ca gihiniyo "
"odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo ārādhikā;"
msgstr ""
"But because Master Gotama, monks, nuns, celibate laymen, laymen enjoying "
"sensual pleasures, celibate laywomen, and laywomen enjoying sensual "
"pleasures have all succeeded in this teaching,"

msgctxt "mn73:13.24"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena."
msgstr "this spiritual path is complete in that respect."

# For the imagery, see SN 12.27, etc.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.494"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:13.25"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, gaṅgā nadī samuddaninnā samuddapoṇā samuddapabbhārā "
"samuddaṃ āhacca tiṭṭhati, evamevāyaṃ bhoto gotamassa parisā "
"sagahaṭṭhapabbajitā nibbānaninnā nibbānapoṇā nibbānapabbhārā nibbānaṃ āhacca "
"tiṭṭhati."
msgstr ""
"Just as the Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines towards the ocean, and "
"keeps pushing into the ocean, in the same way Master Gotama’s assembly—with "
"both laypeople and renunciates—slants, slopes, and inclines towards "
"extinguishment, and keeps pushing into extinguishment."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:15.1"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …"
msgstr "Excellent, Master Gotama! …"

msgctxt "mn73:15.2"
msgid "esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn73:15.3"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāhaṃ bhoto gotamassa santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:16.1"
msgid ""
"“Yo kho, vaccha, aññatitthiyapubbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhati pabbajjaṃ, "
"ākaṅkhati upasampadaṃ, so cattāro māse parivasati. Catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena "
"āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya;"
msgstr ""
"“Vaccha, if someone formerly ordained in another sect wishes to take the "
"going forth, the ordination in this teaching and training, they must spend "
"four months on probation. When four months have passed, if the mendicants "
"are satisfied, they’ll give the going forth, the ordination into monkhood."

msgctxt "mn73:16.2"
msgid "api ca mettha puggalavemattatā viditā”ti."
msgstr "However, I have recognized individual differences in this matter.”"

msgctxt "mn73:16.3"
msgid ""
"“Sace, bhante, aññatitthiyapubbā imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhantā pabbajjaṃ, "
"ākaṅkhantā upasampadaṃ cattāro māse parivasanti, catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena "
"āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya; ahaṃ cattāri "
"vassāni parivasissāmi. Catunnaṃ vassānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū "
"pabbājentu upasampādentu bhikkhubhāvāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, if four months probation are required in such a case, I’ll spend four "
"years on probation. When four years have passed, if the mendicants are "
"satisfied, let them give me the going forth, the ordination into monkhood.”"

msgctxt "mn73:16.4"
msgid ""
"Alattha kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ alattha "
"upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the wanderer Vaccha received the going forth, the ordination in the "
"Buddha’s presence."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:17.1"
msgid ""
"Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā vacchagotto addhamāsūpasampanno yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā vacchagotto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Not long after his ordination, a fortnight later, Venerable Vacchagotta went "
"to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn73:17.2"
msgid ""
"“yāvatakaṃ, bhante, sekhena ñāṇena sekhāya vijjāya pattabbaṃ, anuppattaṃ taṃ "
"mayā;"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I’ve reached as far as possible with the knowledge and understanding "
"of a trainee."

#. VAR: uttari ca me → uttariṃ me (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn73:17.3"
msgid "uttari ca me bhagavā dhammaṃ desetū”ti."
msgstr "Please teach me further.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:18.1"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi tvaṃ, vaccha, dve dhamme uttari bhāvehi—samathañca vipassanañca."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, Vaccha, further develop two things: serenity and discernment."

msgctxt "mn73:18.2"
msgid ""
"Ime kho te, vaccha, dve dhammā uttari bhāvitā—samatho ca vipassanā ca—"
"anekadhātupaṭivedhāya saṃvattissanti."
msgstr ""
"When you have further developed these two things, they’ll lead to the "
"penetration of many elements."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
#. VAR: yāvadeva → yāvade (pts1)
msgctxt "mn73:19.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:"
msgstr ""
"Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and "
"every case:"

msgctxt "mn73:19.2"
msgid ""
"‘anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhaveyyaṃ—ekopi hutvā bahudhā assaṃ, "
"bahudhāpi hutvā eko assaṃ; āvibhāvaṃ, tirobhāvaṃ; tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ "
"tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gaccheyyaṃ, seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi "
"ummujjanimujjaṃ kareyyaṃ, seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gaccheyyaṃ, "
"seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kameyyaṃ, seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo;"
" imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parimaseyyaṃ, "
"parimajjeyyaṃ; yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteyyan’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘May I wield the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying myself and "
"becoming one again; appearing and disappearing; going unimpeded through a "
"wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space; diving in and out of the "
"earth as if it were water; walking on water as if it were earth; flying "
"cross-legged through the sky like a bird; touching and stroking with my hand "
"the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful; controlling my body as far as the "
"Brahmā realm.’"

msgctxt "mn73:19.3"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.495"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:20.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:"
msgstr ""
"Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and "
"every case:"

msgctxt "mn73:20.2"
msgid ""
"‘dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇeyyaṃ—"
"dibbe ca mānuse ca, ye dūre santike cā’ti, tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ "
"pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (2)"
msgstr ""
"‘With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, may I hear both kinds "
"of sounds, human and divine, whether near or far.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:21.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:"
msgstr ""
"Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and "
"every case:"

msgctxt "mn73:21.2"
msgid ""
"‘parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajāneyyaṃ—sarāgaṃ vā "
"cittaṃ sarāgaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ vītarāgaṃ cittanti "
"pajāneyyaṃ; sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ sadosaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītadosaṃ vā "
"cittaṃ vītadosaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; samohaṃ vā cittaṃ samohaṃ cittanti "
"pajāneyyaṃ, vītamohaṃ vā cittaṃ vītamohaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; saṅkhittaṃ vā "
"cittaṃ saṅkhittaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ vikkhittaṃ "
"cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ mahaggataṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, "
"amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ amahaggataṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ "
"sauttaraṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ anuttaraṃ cittanti "
"pajāneyyaṃ; samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ samāhitaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, asamāhitaṃ vā "
"cittaṃ asamāhitaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ cittanti "
"pajāneyyaṃ, avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ avimuttaṃ cittanti pajāneyyan’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘May I understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having "
"comprehended them with my mind. May I understand mind with greed as “mind "
"with greed”, and mind without greed as “mind without greed”; mind with hate "
"as “mind with hate”, and mind without hate as “mind without hate”; mind with "
"delusion as “mind with delusion”, and mind without delusion as “mind without "
"delusion”; contracted mind as “contracted mind”, and scattered mind as “"
"scattered mind”; expansive mind as “expansive mind”, and unexpansive mind as "
"“unexpansive mind”; mind that is not supreme as “mind that is not supreme”, "
"and mind that is supreme as “mind that is supreme”; mind immersed in samādhi "
"as “mind immersed in samādhi”, and mind not immersed in samādhi as “mind not "
"immersed in samādhi”; freed mind as “freed mind”, and unfreed mind as “"
"unfreed mind”.’"

msgctxt "mn73:21.3"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:22.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:"
msgstr ""
"Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and "
"every case:"

msgctxt "mn73:22.2"
msgid ""
"‘anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussareyyaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi "
"jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi "
"jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi "
"jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi; anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi "
"vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe—amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto "
"evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato "
"cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapannoti; "
"iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussareyyan’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘May I recollect many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, "
"five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred "
"thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the "
"world evolving, many eons of the world contracting and evolving. May I "
"remember: “There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, "
"and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was "
"how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere "
"else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, "
"and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was "
"how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.” "
"May I recollect my many past lives, with features and details.’"

msgctxt "mn73:22.3"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.496"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:23.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:"
msgstr ""
"Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and "
"every case:"

msgctxt "mn73:23.2"
msgid ""
"‘dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passeyyaṃ cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage "
"satte pajāneyyaṃ—ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā "
"vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā "
"micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā; ime vā pana bhonto sattā "
"kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena "
"samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannāti; iti dibbena "
"cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passeyyaṃ cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage "
"satte pajāneyyan’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, may I see sentient "
"beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and "
"ugly, in a good place or a bad place—and understand how sentient beings are "
"reborn according to their deeds: “These dear beings did bad things by way of "
"body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong "
"view; and they chose to act out of that wrong view. When their body breaks "
"up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the "
"underworld, hell. These dear beings, however, did good things by way of "
"body, speech, and mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had "
"right view; and they chose to act out of that right view. When their body "
"breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.” "
"And so, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, may I see "
"sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, "
"beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. And may I understand how "
"sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.’"

msgctxt "mn73:23.3"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:24.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:"
msgstr ""
"Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and "
"every case:"

msgctxt "mn73:24.2"
msgid ""
"‘āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyan’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘May I realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this "
"very life, and live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending "
"of defilements.’"

msgctxt "mn73:24.3"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane”ti. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:25.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā vacchagotto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā "
"uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"And then Venerable Vacchagotta approved and agreed with what the Buddha "
"said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, "
"keeping him on his right, before leaving."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:26.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā vacchagotto eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto "
"viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then Vacchagotta, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, "
"soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He "
"lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which people from "
"good families rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

msgctxt "mn73:26.2"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”"

msgctxt "mn73:26.3"
msgid "Aññataro kho panāyasmā vacchagotto arahataṃ ahosi."
msgstr "And Venerable Vacchagotta became one of the perfected."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.497"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:27.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ dassanāya gacchanti."
msgstr "Now at that time several mendicants were going to see the Buddha."

msgctxt "mn73:27.2"
msgid "Addasā kho āyasmā vacchagotto te bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante."
msgstr "Vacchagotta saw them coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "mn73:27.3"
msgid ""
"Disvāna yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr "went up to them, and said:"

msgctxt "mn73:27.4"
msgid "“handa kahaṃ pana tumhe āyasmanto gacchathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Hello venerables, where are you going?”"

msgctxt "mn73:27.5"
msgid "“Bhagavantaṃ kho mayaṃ, āvuso, dassanāya gacchāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Reverend, we are going to see the Buddha.”"

msgctxt "mn73:27.6"
msgid ""
"“Tenahāyasmanto mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatha, evañca vadetha:"
msgstr ""
"“Well then, reverends, in my name please bow with your head to the Buddha’s "
"feet and say:"

msgctxt "mn73:27.7"
msgid ""
"‘vacchagotto, bhante, bhikkhu bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, evañca vadeti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, the mendicant Vacchagotta bows with his head to your feet and says:"

msgctxt "mn73:27.8"
msgid "pariciṇṇo me bhagavā, pariciṇṇo me sugato’”ti."
msgstr "“I have served the Blessed One! I have served the Holy One!”’”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:28.1"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato vacchagottassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn73:28.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then those mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn73:28.3"
msgid ""
"“āyasmā, bhante, vacchagotto bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, evañca vadeti:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the mendicant Vacchagotta bows with his head to your feet and says:"

msgctxt "mn73:28.4"
msgid "‘pariciṇṇo me bhagavā, pariciṇṇo me sugato’”ti."
msgstr "‘I have served the Blessed One! I have served the Holy One!’”"

msgctxt "mn73:28.5"
msgid "“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, vacchagotto bhikkhu cetasā ceto paricca vidito:"
msgstr "“I’ve already comprehended Vacchagotta’s mind and understood that"

msgctxt "mn73:28.6"
msgid "‘tevijjo vacchagotto bhikkhu mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo’ti."
msgstr "he has the three knowledges, and is very mighty and powerful."

msgctxt "mn73:28.7"
msgid "Devatāpi me etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ:"
msgstr "And deities also told me.”"

msgctxt "mn73:28.8"
msgid "‘tevijjo, bhante, vacchagotto bhikkhu mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn73:28.9"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn73:28.10"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn73:28.11"
msgid "Mahāvacchasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
